-- BREAKINGVIEWS-Edward Hadas: The ongoing ethics struggle of banks
-- 
-- Wed Mar 05, 2014 10:45AM EST
-- None



NEW YORK, March 5 (Reuters) - The boss of Credit Suisse blamed a few private bankers for recent U.S. legal problems. The Employees Association wants management to take more responsibility. Such blame-casting misses the point. In too many businesses, the culture encourages ignoring the voice of conscience.

